Blocks.childText: 134 The Fairy Crowning. Continued. (Enter six Fairies, three at right and three at left. Running lightly in, they form a semi-circle facing before the throne in the center. They salute the Queen as they enter by bowing very low. Play first strain of Introduction as the Fairies enter. The Fairies should step four times for each measure, and thus keep exact time.) Moderato. QUEEN. (Addressing the extreme right.) My dear lit - tle fay Where were you to - day? And what have you done and seen; Some one lit - tle sprite, Shall crowned be to-night With this myr - tle wreath pret - ty and green.
